description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Our Trust has an amazing story to tell. Every day we make a difference to people&#39;s lives, supporting them through difficult times. We are looking for a Communications Officer to bring that story to life, helping to ensure colleagues understand how their work makes a vital contribution to our vision.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;You&#39;ll need to have sound news judgement, be able to inspire with imaginative campaigns and make the most out of every story. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will need to be a shrewd stakeholder manager who can advise on messaging, channels and tone to help us engage with a wide variety of audiences.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;You&#39;ll help colleagues celebrate success and achievement through inspiring events and engagement, helping to develop a sense of pride in the workplace.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are working in unprecedented times due to the global pandemic and communication is at the centre of ensuring our teams, our service users and their carers are as safe as possible. We need someone who can hit the ground running, work at pace in an ever-changing situation and effectively prioritise a busy workload.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;In return, we are offering a rewarding career with a competitive salary. Additional perks of working for us include the option to buy additional holidays, tax and national insurance-efficient initiatives and a range of training and services to help support physical and mental wellbeing.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;If you’re passionate about communication, have a ‘can-do’ attitude and want a role where you can make a real difference, we want to hear from you.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sam Thomas by emailing sam.thomas@lscft.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
